The paper focuses on the implementation of a user interface for task-based industrial robot programming, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. The use of different input and output modalities for intuitive interaction suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect. The paper also mentions the use of a semantic description for automatically inferring required system components, which suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) aspect. The evaluation of different input modalities for interaction suggests a software development (cs.SD) aspect. Finally, the user study conducted for the evaluation suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) aspect.
